A vintage 1940s noir-style scene showing a shadowy figure in a fedora and trench coat sitting alone in an ornate movie theater, bathed in the dramatic glow of a film projector beam, while clutching a bucket of popcorn protectively to their chest. The theater seats around them are empty, and the projection booth window looms ominously above like an accusatory eye. Rich sepia tones with deep shadows and film grain texture, evoking classic detective movie posters. The atmosphere feels paranoid and absurd simultaneously, as if an innocent moviegoer has been cast as a suspect in their own entertainment experience.
